metadata.name: FAT Christmas #172
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.

metadata.name: Joy Spaces #66
metadata.description:
Sharing a space that fills us with happiness
    Exploring what is deeply inside 
    Thinking as one and thinking as hive
    We play
    A doing so we transcend

    I know you as you know me
    You explore as I explore
    Mirrors of fears to grow
    Mirrors of love to embrace
    Let's keep on as we can
    Discovering the unknown
    That explodes inside each of us
    And is asking to be felt



Controls: 's' - canvas save

Crafted to be seen in Google Chrome 107.0.5304.107

Released on fx(hash) to celebrate the first birthday of this platform that has transformed our lives and our culture. Thank you mates, developers, artist and collectors. It has been a great year and I hope is the first of many to came. 


(c) Victor Doval; all rights reserved

metadata.name: Artifice #14
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Circumscript #188
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.

metadata.name: Rough Cuts #28
metadata.description:
Abstract generative artwork that explores composition and form by cutting canvas with straight lines. Coded brushwork gives a real-painting look to each piece.

Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, July, 2022.

metadata.name: Unrestrained #127
metadata.description:
I am revolving yet static,
at once simple and emphatic.
My rules are maintained,
Yet by my frame I'm unrestrained.

This is a generative piece made in p5.js.

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #22
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Abstract Hedonism #81
metadata.description:
Abstraction is the beauty of pure geometry and mathematics.

That project was inspired by fathers of minimalism and suprematism, such as the : El Lissitzky, Kazimir Malevich, Pit Mondrian, Paul Klee, etc.

My main goal was to learn how to work with Perlin noise, implement it in different formats and compositions.

Project contains:

•Various formats and orientations of the canvas: from 100 to 1900 pixels
•Carefully selected color palettes with rare BLACK ones
•Fully random animation
•Press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous

metadata.name: A Distant Memory #109
metadata.description:
A distant memory of trees, buildings and the old village. Once a moment, the memory is illuminated by a beam of light, which gives me the insight of this work.

--------------------

This is an abstract generation made by pure code.

--------------------

In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take one minute in my computer).
This is my last artwork in 2022. I hope you like this work.

Endlessworld 2022

metadata.description:
"Think that it is likely to happen or be"

Subjective lines and squads on the noise canvas.
